<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="7" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[192,1441,1519,1929]" lastBlockId="8.[192,1440,221,437]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="7" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,568,1519,1544]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">
Description. Male 
<typeStatus box="[440,562,1520,1544]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity box="[667,760,1520,1544]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="2.3">2.3 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[846,939,1520,1544]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="2.1">2.1 mm</quantity>
; dorsal surface shiny except head densely alutaceous. Color black; pronotum with lateral 1/4, apical 1/4 yellow; elytron with wide, yellow lateral margin enlarged into incipient macula on apical declivity, in addition an irregularly oval macula present medially in basal 1/2 (
<figureCitation box="[461,546,1616,1640]" captionStart="Figures 18–34" captionStartId="22.[192,287,1819,1841]" captionTargetBox="[206,1432,318,1691]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[192,1440,304,1737]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figures 18–34. Pentilia spp. 18-23) Pentilia nichole. 18) Habitus. 19) Frons. 20) Penis guide ventral. 21) Penis guide lateral. 22) Penis. 23) Spermathecal capsule 24-29) Pentilia jody. 24) Habitus. 25) Frons. 26) Penis guide ventral. 27) Penis guide lateral. 28) Penis. 29-34) Pentilia kendra. 29) Habitus. 30) Frons. 31) Penis guide ventral. 32) Penis guide lateral. 33) Penis. 34) Spermathecal capsule." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3675049" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3675049/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
); venter yellow; abdomen yellow except apex of basal abdominal ventrite. Head punctures not visible, hidden in alutaceous sculpture; pronotal punctures small, separated by less than to 3 times a diameter; elytral punctures larger than on pronotum, separated by less than to 4 times a diameter, becoming larger, denser toward lateral margin; prosternum with small punctures separated by less than a diameter; mesosternum with coarse punctures separated by a diameter or less; metasternum with punctures smaller than on mesosternum, separated by 1 to 3 times a diameter in median 3/4, punctures becoming absent in lateral 1/4; abdominal ventrites 1, 2 with coarse punctures separated by less than to twice a diameter; ventrites 3–4 finely, densely punctured medially; ventrite 5 finely, densely punctured. Head with frons parallel sided, 1.2 times as wide as eye, clypeal apex widely emarginate, lateral angle abruptly curved (
<figureCitation box="[708,791,1904,1929]" captionStart="Figures 18–34" captionStartId="22.[192,287,1819,1841]" captionTargetBox="[206,1432,318,1691]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[192,1440,304,1737]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figures 18–34. Pentilia spp. 18-23) Pentilia nichole. 18) Habitus. 19) Frons. 20) Penis guide ventral. 21) Penis guide lateral. 22) Penis. 23) Spermathecal capsule 24-29) Pentilia jody. 24) Habitus. 25) Frons. 26) Penis guide ventral. 27) Penis guide lateral. 28) Penis. 29-34) Pentilia kendra. 29) Habitus. 30) Frons. 31) Penis guide ventral. 32) Penis guide lateral. 33) Penis. 34) Spermathecal capsule." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3675049" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3675049/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
); eye canthus long, about 3/4 width of eye. Prosternum with lateral carina on each side short, straight, extended from apex of intercoxal process 1/4 distance to apex of prosternum. Epipleuron strongly descending externally. Postcoxal line on basal abdominal ventrite slightly flattened along posterior ventrite margin, extended 7/8 distance to rear margin of ventrite. Genitalia with basal lobe as long as paramere, sides gradually narrowed from base to abruptly rounded apex; paramere slender, nearly straight, apex rounded (
<figureCitation box="[984,1114,349,373]" captionStart="Figures 18–34" captionStartId="22.[192,287,1819,1841]" captionTargetBox="[206,1432,318,1691]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[192,1440,304,1737]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figures 18–34. Pentilia spp. 18-23) Pentilia nichole. 18) Habitus. 19) Frons. 20) Penis guide ventral. 21) Penis guide lateral. 22) Penis. 23) Spermathecal capsule 24-29) Pentilia jody. 24) Habitus. 25) Frons. 26) Penis guide ventral. 27) Penis guide lateral. 28) Penis. 29-34) Pentilia kendra. 29) Habitus. 30) Frons. 31) Penis guide ventral. 32) Penis guide lateral. 33) Penis. 34) Spermathecal capsule." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3675049" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3675049/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Fig. 20, 21</figureCitation>
); penis with apical portion divided; basal capsule slender, inner arm long slightly curved, apex truncate, outer arm long, straight, apex abruptly curved (
<figureCitation box="[468,556,413,437]" captionStart="Figures 18–34" captionStartId="22.[192,287,1819,1841]" captionTargetBox="[206,1432,318,1691]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[192,1440,304,1737]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figures 18–34. Pentilia spp. 18-23) Pentilia nichole. 18) Habitus. 19) Frons. 20) Penis guide ventral. 21) Penis guide lateral. 22) Penis. 23) Spermathecal capsule 24-29) Pentilia jody. 24) Habitus. 25) Frons. 26) Penis guide ventral. 27) Penis guide lateral. 28) Penis. 29-34) Pentilia kendra. 29) Habitus. 30) Frons. 31) Penis guide ventral. 32) Penis guide lateral. 33) Penis. 34) Spermathecal capsule." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3675049" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3675049/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[192,1440,458,515]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,300,458,482]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Female.</emphasis>
Similar to male except spermathecal capsule slender, ramus not enlarged, cornu evenly curved to rounded apex (
<figureCitation box="[405,492,490,515]" captionStart="Figures 18–34" captionStartId="22.[192,287,1819,1841]" captionTargetBox="[206,1432,318,1691]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[192,1440,304,1737]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figures 18–34. Pentilia spp. 18-23) Pentilia nichole. 18) Habitus. 19) Frons. 20) Penis guide ventral. 21) Penis guide lateral. 22) Penis. 23) Spermathecal capsule 24-29) Pentilia jody. 24) Habitus. 25) Frons. 26) Penis guide ventral. 27) Penis guide lateral. 28) Penis. 29-34) Pentilia kendra. 29) Habitus. 30) Frons. 31) Penis guide ventral. 32) Penis guide lateral. 33) Penis. 34) Spermathecal capsule." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3675049" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3675049/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[192,1440,535,592]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,331,535,559]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Variation.</emphasis>
Length 2.0 to 
<quantity box="[515,611,536,560]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="2.4">2.4 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[705,880,536,560]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.05" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="2.05" valueMax="2.3" valueMin="1.8">1.8 to 2.3 mm</quantity>
. Pronotal color varies from entirely yellow to lateral 1/3 yellow with all intergrades between, size and shape of elytral maculae vary slightly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
