<paragraph blockId="8.[192,1440,755,843]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,323,755,779]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is possibly conspecific with 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Gordon and Gonzalez" authorityYear="2019" box="[830,921,755,778]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Pentilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="traci">
<emphasis box="[830,848,755,778]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[864,921,755,778]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">traci</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in spite of the quite different dorsal color patterns. The male genitalia are virtually identical and both are from 
<collectingCountry box="[1057,1136,787,811]" name="Brazil" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. They are maintained as separate species because of the different color patterns.
</paragraph>
